WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.750
Dre: When I was a kid,

00:03.750 --> 00:06.250
art was just a bunch
of old white guys from Europe

00:06.250 --> 00:09.000
painting other old white guys.

00:09.000 --> 00:12.000
And then I saw
my first Basquiat.

00:12.000 --> 00:13.210
It was art,

00:13.210 --> 00:15.290
but it was also
confrontational,

00:15.290 --> 00:16.580
revolutionary,

00:16.580 --> 00:19.790
and somehow undeniably black.

00:19.790 --> 00:22.250
It changed everything
for me,

00:22.250 --> 00:25.960
and because of that,
my house is festooned

00:25.960 --> 00:29.170
with the works of prominent
African-American artists.

00:29.170 --> 00:32.380
"Soul Power" by Fahamu Pecou.

00:32.380 --> 00:35.380
A bold painting
by a bold artist.

00:35.380 --> 00:38.080
Oh, I love this one
because it tells the world

00:38.080 --> 00:40.330
that black people can swim,

00:40.330 --> 00:42.000
even though I can't.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.710
And this is one
of the last pieces

00:44.710 --> 00:48.710
the great Noah Davis did
before he passed away.

00:48.710 --> 00:50.750
And the man
who did Obama's portrait

00:50.750 --> 00:52.500
did my T-shirt,

00:52.500 --> 00:54.580
because Kehinde Wiley
is smart enough

00:54.580 --> 00:56.960
to get paid
while he's still alive.

00:56.960 --> 00:58.790
Good morning, family.

00:58.790 --> 01:01.170
Morning, babe.
Mm.

01:01.170 --> 01:04.330
Notice anything different
about me?

01:04.330 --> 01:06.250
Hmm.
You're getting less needy?

01:06.250 --> 01:08.880
No, can't be that.
Jack: Mm.

01:08.880 --> 01:12.830
♪♪

01:12.830 --> 01:14.380
How is it possible

01:14.380 --> 01:16.830
that in a house
so full of people,

01:16.830 --> 01:20.880
I can feel so alone...
and so cold?

01:20.880 --> 01:24.960
[ Speaking French ]

01:24.960 --> 01:26.380
Lynette: Dre?

01:26.380 --> 01:30.170
Is this
an original Noah Davis?

01:31.580 --> 01:32.540
Oui, Lynette.

01:38.750 --> 01:40.040
I never knew

01:40.040 --> 01:42.170
you were
an art lover.
Oh.

01:42.170 --> 01:45.000
Lynette loves anything
that gets better with age, son.

01:45.000 --> 01:46.750
Wine, art, moi.

01:46.750 --> 01:48.830
[ Both laugh ]

01:48.830 --> 01:52.420
I have a bachelor's degree
in Visual Arts from Spelman.

01:52.420 --> 01:54.580
I wanted to study
Art History,

01:54.580 --> 01:55.670
but they talked me
out of it.

01:55.670 --> 01:57.210
Oh, boy.
Pops:
One of the last things

01:57.210 --> 01:58.920
me and Ruby agreed on.
Mm-hmm.

01:58.920 --> 02:01.290
That and that cheese
is not a dessert,

02:01.290 --> 02:02.620
no matter
what Europe says.

02:02.620 --> 02:04.960
[ Laughs ]

02:04.960 --> 02:06.670
We did you a favor, son.

02:06.670 --> 02:09.210
Name me one successful
Black artist.

02:09.210 --> 02:12.120
Unh-unh. Besides the guy who
makes them happy little trees.

02:12.120 --> 02:12.920
Mama,
I keep telling you,

02:12.920 --> 02:14.620
we cannot claim Bob Ross

02:14.620 --> 02:15.880
just because
he has an afro.

02:15.880 --> 02:17.670
He ain't one of us.

02:17.670 --> 02:20.830
Well, I'm gonna have to see
his mama before I'm convinced.

02:20.830 --> 02:22.120
[ Laughing ] Believe.
Think about it.

02:22.120 --> 02:23.750
That right? Hey.

02:23.750 --> 02:26.330
This is
what I was born into.

02:26.330 --> 02:28.580
Well, Dre,
don't listen to them.

02:28.580 --> 02:31.420
Thank you.
You and Rainbow
have great taste.

02:31.420 --> 02:32.960
Okay, first off, Rainbow
has horrible taste.

02:32.960 --> 02:33.830
That's all me.

02:33.830 --> 02:35.420
[ Gasps ]
Alright?

02:35.420 --> 02:38.330
She wanted to hang
stupid family pictures up.

02:38.330 --> 02:40.830
Whoa, wait.
You chose all those paintings?

02:40.830 --> 02:42.330
I thought
they came with the house.

02:42.330 --> 02:45.170
[ Sighs ] I tried
to take these philistines

02:45.170 --> 02:47.620
to the Kerry James Marshall
exhibit, but no.

02:47.620 --> 02:49.960
They wanted to go
to a birthday party

02:49.960 --> 02:52.170
at a trampoline park.

02:52.170 --> 02:55.170
The trampoline park had pictures
of people on the trampoline.

02:55.170 --> 02:57.040
That's art, too, Dad.
[ Groans ]

02:57.040 --> 02:59.750
And I got to see the Mona Lisa
of ankle breaks.
Mm-hmm.

02:59.750 --> 03:01.210
The way his wife laughed

03:01.210 --> 03:03.000
after he hurt himself?
[ Chuckles ]

03:03.000 --> 03:04.580
They're probably divorced
by now.
Oh, yeah.

03:04.580 --> 03:07.290
Andre, if you ever want
to talk about art,

03:07.290 --> 03:08.710
you can do it with me.

03:08.710 --> 03:09.960
Really?

03:09.960 --> 03:13.080
Oh, it is one
of my favorite things.

03:13.080 --> 03:15.500
I am a member at LACMA...
Ooh.

03:15.500 --> 03:17.540
...The Hammer,
The Broad...

03:17.540 --> 03:19.580
The California
African American Museum?

03:19.580 --> 03:22.420
I have a plaque
at the plaza.

03:22.420 --> 03:23.460
A plaque in the plaza?

03:23.460 --> 03:25.540
Right between
George Lucas' wife

03:25.540 --> 03:27.040
and Robert De Niro's wife.

03:27.040 --> 03:29.290
This...is amazing.
[ Chuckles ]

03:29.290 --> 03:30.880
Lynette, you're amazing!

03:30.880 --> 03:32.380
Okay, okay, okay.

03:32.380 --> 03:33.830
Get your own fiancée.

03:33.830 --> 03:35.790
She's amazing, Pops.
We have to go now.

03:35.790 --> 03:38.170
Lynette has to referee
the Urban League's

03:38.170 --> 03:39.750
annual charity
basketball game.
[ Snorts, chuckles ]

03:39.750 --> 03:40.920
Oh. Okay.
Say goodbye, baby.

03:40.920 --> 03:42.460
Oh, bye.

03:42.460 --> 03:44.080
But I loved catching up
with you.

03:44.080 --> 03:46.040
Oh.
I love you, too.

03:49.210 --> 03:50.580
What'd you say?
I -- I-I --

03:50.580 --> 03:51.880
As in the band, U2.

03:51.880 --> 03:55.290
I love U2, UB40, Us3,

03:55.290 --> 03:56.380
anything with a "U" in it,
Pops.

03:56.380 --> 03:58.290
Mm-hmm.

03:58.290 --> 03:59.710
"You Be Illin'."

03:59.710 --> 04:00.880
Yeah! Huh!

04:00.880 --> 04:02.040
Get off me!

04:02.040 --> 04:03.250
No! Get away!

04:03.250 --> 04:04.120
Rainbow:
I've got pepper spray!

04:04.120 --> 04:05.120
I've got pepper spray!

04:05.120 --> 04:06.290
Wait -- What --

04:06.290 --> 04:07.920
No, Mom, Mom,
I'm -- I'm fine.

04:07.920 --> 04:09.540
It's -- It's just a game.

04:09.540 --> 04:11.790
Right now, I'm defending
a children's hospital

04:11.790 --> 04:13.540
from the undead.

04:13.540 --> 04:15.620
Seen a lot of awful things
in those halls.
Hmm.

04:15.620 --> 04:17.670
But I've also seen
a lot of hope.
Hmm.

04:17.670 --> 04:18.960
You want to join?

04:18.960 --> 04:21.670
Oh, I'd love to, but no.
Mnh-mnh.

04:21.670 --> 04:23.710
I just made myself
a pot of tea,

04:23.710 --> 04:25.500
and I'm gonna read a book.

04:25.500 --> 04:27.380
Uh, come on, Mom.

04:27.380 --> 04:28.620
We both have the day off.

04:28.620 --> 04:29.670
Wouldn't it be great to do

04:29.670 --> 04:31.790
some mother-son
zombie-busting?

04:31.790 --> 04:34.080
Okay, well, we can agree
to disagree on that one...

04:34.080 --> 04:37.500
Mm.
...and you can agree
to put all of this...

04:37.500 --> 04:39.500
back when you're done.

04:39.500 --> 04:40.750
Okay.
Yeah?

04:40.750 --> 04:42.960
I promise I will put
everything back perfectly

04:42.960 --> 04:45.710
as soon as all of the children
are safe and sound.

04:45.710 --> 04:47.460
Whatever.
Okay?

04:47.460 --> 04:48.460
Alright.

04:48.460 --> 04:49.710
We are back in the ga--

04:49.710 --> 04:51.330
Uhp. I'm dead.

04:51.330 --> 04:52.500
Alright.

04:52.500 --> 04:55.210
Hey, guys.
This is good news.

04:55.210 --> 04:57.670
The vape industry will pay us
a lot of money

04:57.670 --> 05:00.290
if we can rehabilitate
their image

05:00.290 --> 05:02.790
by proving their product
is not for kids.

05:02.790 --> 05:05.080
Now, how do we market

05:05.080 --> 05:06.960
gummy-bear-flavored tobacco
for adults?
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

05:06.960 --> 05:07.960
Go.

05:07.960 --> 05:09.920
[ Laughs ]
Chewy smoke.

05:09.920 --> 05:10.830
Okay, Dre,
what do you got?

05:10.830 --> 05:11.920
You got something?

05:11.920 --> 05:13.040
Oh, no, no, no,
no, no.

05:13.040 --> 05:14.620
I just got a text
from Lynette.

05:14.620 --> 05:16.330
Oh, okay.

05:16.330 --> 05:19.000
[ Chuckles ]
So, it finally happened, huh?

05:19.000 --> 05:20.290
What finally happened?

05:20.290 --> 05:21.620
You got yourself
a mistress.

05:21.620 --> 05:22.540
Well done.
What?

05:22.540 --> 05:24.170
No, man.

05:24.170 --> 05:26.790
Lynette
is my father's fiancée.

05:26.790 --> 05:27.960
-Oh.
-Oh. Oh. I'm sorry.

05:27.960 --> 05:29.790
No, we're both fans
of Black art.

05:29.790 --> 05:31.080
Okay. Sorry.
Oh.

05:31.080 --> 05:32.120
So am I.

05:32.120 --> 05:33.670
Word?
Yeah.

05:33.670 --> 05:35.750
Airbrushed pictures
of dead rappers,

05:35.750 --> 05:39.210
Maya Angelou quotes on plywood
in pretty fonts,

05:39.210 --> 05:41.250
oil paintings
of naked women in afros

05:41.250 --> 05:43.170
posing with various
big cats.

05:43.170 --> 05:45.120
Okay, that's not what
I was talking about, Charlie.

05:45.120 --> 05:47.500
I'm talking
about Black artists.

05:47.500 --> 05:49.670
Oh.
Fine artists

05:49.670 --> 05:51.460
whose works
are in museums.

05:51.460 --> 05:54.620
You know, like Charles White,
uh, and Emory Douglas.

05:54.620 --> 05:56.120
You guys know
who I'm talking about, right?

05:56.120 --> 05:58.120
Obviously,
we don't know them, Dre.

05:58.120 --> 05:59.380
And the fact
that you're even asking

05:59.380 --> 06:01.250
makes me wonder
if you even know us.

06:01.250 --> 06:02.460
Okay.

06:02.460 --> 06:04.000
How about Basquiat?

06:04.000 --> 06:05.420
Everybody knows Basquiat.

06:05.420 --> 06:06.830
Mm.
The cheese?

06:06.830 --> 06:09.580
This is insane.

06:09.580 --> 06:12.210
You don't know
who Jean-Michel Basquiat is?

06:12.210 --> 06:15.460
He brought street art
into the fine art world

06:15.460 --> 06:17.460
decades before Banksy.

06:17.460 --> 06:20.790
Uh -- Kara Walker's
nightmarish silhouettes

06:20.790 --> 06:24.540
tells the story
of American slavery and racism.

06:24.540 --> 06:26.580
So sad.
I'm sorry,
I don't -- I don't know.

06:26.580 --> 06:29.920
This is where I am.

06:29.920 --> 06:33.540
I can't talk to one person
about one of my greatest loves.

06:33.540 --> 06:34.880
Sweaters?

06:34.880 --> 06:35.670
Cannolis?

06:35.670 --> 06:38.290
Art.

06:38.290 --> 06:39.500
You know what?
This is crazy.

06:39.500 --> 06:40.670
You know what?
I'm just gonna call Lynette

06:40.670 --> 06:43.420
and ask her if she wants
to go to a gallery.

06:43.420 --> 06:44.620
She understands me.

06:44.620 --> 06:45.920
You go, Dre.

06:45.920 --> 06:47.040
You go be with her.

06:47.040 --> 06:48.670
And while you're at it
[Clears throat]

06:48.670 --> 06:52.120
bring me back a painting
of a woman with a white tiger.

06:52.120 --> 06:54.420
Matter of fact,
here's $40.

06:54.420 --> 06:56.290
Get me one
that lights up.

06:56.290 --> 06:58.920
So, Lynette and I
got together,

06:58.920 --> 07:00.620
and going to a gallery

07:00.620 --> 07:03.290
with someone
who loved art as much as I did

07:03.290 --> 07:06.250
was everything
I hoped it would be.

07:06.250 --> 07:07.960
It was a great day,

07:07.960 --> 07:10.540
and there was one way
to make it perfect.

07:10.540 --> 07:12.500
It's been a minute

07:12.500 --> 07:15.000
since I've been
to The Cheesecake Machine.
[ Chuckles ]

07:15.000 --> 07:18.040
This is me and my mama's
favorite spot.
Oh.

07:18.040 --> 07:20.290
You know, I love how they put
a whole fried chicken

07:20.290 --> 07:22.040
on a leaf of iceberg

07:22.040 --> 07:23.500
and call it a salad.

07:23.500 --> 07:24.670
[ Both laugh ]

07:24.670 --> 07:26.880
It's hard to find
a 5,000-calorie salad

07:26.880 --> 07:27.790
in this town.

07:27.790 --> 07:29.040
It ain't Georgia.

07:29.040 --> 07:30.540
[ Laughs ]

07:30.540 --> 07:33.380
I see somebody's eyes
were bigger than his stomach.

07:33.380 --> 07:35.460
I told you not to fill up
on that bread.

07:35.460 --> 07:38.170
Now, we have a bit of a ride
to get back home.

07:38.170 --> 07:41.750
When was the last time
you went to the bathroom?

07:41.750 --> 07:43.290
I went at the gallery.

07:43.290 --> 07:44.830
Did you?

07:44.830 --> 07:45.880
Okay, you know what?
You're right.

07:45.880 --> 07:46.830
I-I should go right now.

07:46.830 --> 07:48.580
Well, hol-- hol-- hold on.
Mm?

07:48.580 --> 07:51.920
There's just a little something
just right there.
Where? Uh-huh?

07:51.920 --> 07:53.000
Ooh. [ Chuckles ]
Mnh.

07:53.000 --> 07:54.290
Got it.
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

07:54.290 --> 07:56.420
Thank you, Mama.

07:56.420 --> 07:57.790
I mean Lynette.

07:57.790 --> 08:00.960
Uh-oh.
I'm not cheating on my wife.

08:00.960 --> 08:03.670
I'm cheating on my mother.

08:03.670 --> 08:06.290
Whoa!
What's happening, Black Jesus?!

08:10.120 --> 08:12.420
[ Sighs ] Wow.
Mm.

08:12.420 --> 08:14.920
You're cheating
on your mother.
Ah.

08:14.920 --> 08:16.620
Congratulations.
Okay.

08:16.620 --> 08:21.040
You moved past Oedipal
and created your own complex.

08:21.040 --> 08:22.380
Okay, here's the thing
about it, Bow.

08:22.380 --> 08:23.380
Hmm?

08:23.380 --> 08:24.960
I kind of liked it.
Ew.

08:24.960 --> 08:26.750
It felt so right.

08:26.750 --> 08:28.210
[ Sighs ]

08:28.210 --> 08:29.960
Lynette does
a thing for me.

08:29.960 --> 08:31.420
Mm.

08:31.420 --> 08:33.540
This is like the worst
Shakespeare play ever.

08:33.540 --> 08:35.500
No, babe,
we had a great day.

08:35.500 --> 08:38.670
Mm.
We genuinely connected
over art.

08:38.670 --> 08:42.290
I didn't realize how much I was
missing it until I found it.

08:42.290 --> 08:43.750
Aww.

08:43.750 --> 08:47.960
Well...too bad you're gonna
have to drop her.

08:47.960 --> 08:50.540
'Cause you know your mom
is easily threatened.

08:50.540 --> 08:52.040
What?

08:52.040 --> 08:53.170
I'll just top this off
for you.

08:53.170 --> 08:55.540
-Okay.
-The hell you will.

08:55.540 --> 08:57.500
You don't know how my baby
likes his beer poured.

08:57.500 --> 08:58.500
Go on,
get out of here.

08:58.500 --> 08:59.710
Okay.

08:59.710 --> 09:00.830
Here, baby.

09:00.830 --> 09:02.750
You alright?
Yes, Mama.

09:02.750 --> 09:04.540
She's mellowed.

09:04.540 --> 09:06.250
Alright, look at how
she's handling

09:06.250 --> 09:07.790
Pops' and Lynette's
relationship.

09:07.790 --> 09:09.210
She's not threatened.

09:09.210 --> 09:10.790
You're just saying that,
Dre,

09:10.790 --> 09:12.620
'cause you want to keep
hanging out with Lynette.

09:12.620 --> 09:14.540
No, Bow, I --

09:14.540 --> 09:16.580
I want you to see it from
my mother's perspective.

09:16.580 --> 09:18.380
Okay.
Okay?

09:18.380 --> 09:21.080
It's half the work, and she
doesn't always have to be on.

09:21.080 --> 09:22.500
Everybody wins.

09:22.500 --> 09:25.040
It's a win-win-win.

09:25.040 --> 09:27.170
Okay, I've expressed
my concerns,

09:27.170 --> 09:29.500
and I've told you how I think
this is going to turn out.

09:29.500 --> 09:31.540
So I have no guilt
in allowing you

09:31.540 --> 09:34.120
to walk
into this situation.

09:34.120 --> 09:36.500
But...

09:36.500 --> 09:37.380
God bless you.

09:37.380 --> 09:38.500
Thank you.
Mm-hmm.

09:38.500 --> 09:40.170
Oh. Hey, Mama.
Ooh.

09:40.170 --> 09:42.250
Um, I'm going to the museum
with Lynette and the kids,

09:42.250 --> 09:44.580
and I would love for you
to come with us.

09:44.580 --> 09:45.920
Oh.
Oh, oh, sorry.

09:45.920 --> 09:47.920
I got my earbuds in.

09:47.920 --> 09:49.710
What did you say,
sweetie?

09:49.710 --> 09:52.080
I said I'm going to the museum
with Lynette and the kids,

09:52.080 --> 09:53.920
and I want you to come.

09:53.920 --> 09:55.540
Sure.
Sounds great.

09:57.210 --> 09:58.080
Does it?

09:58.080 --> 09:59.830
Yeah,
sounds like fun.

09:59.830 --> 10:01.210
[ Chuckles ]
Look at my baby.

10:01.210 --> 10:03.170
Taking his children
and his mama out

10:03.170 --> 10:05.380
for a day
at a classy museum.

10:05.380 --> 10:07.000
Mm-hmm.
Oh, boo.

10:07.000 --> 10:08.330
Mwah.
Mwah.

10:08.330 --> 10:09.210
Thank you, Mama.
Proud of you, baby.

10:09.210 --> 10:10.080
Thank you.
Uh-huh.

10:10.080 --> 10:12.170
[ Chuckles ]

10:12.170 --> 10:13.210
[ Clears throat ]

10:13.210 --> 10:16.330
Having two mamas
is gonna be great.

10:16.330 --> 10:17.670
Hmm.

10:17.670 --> 10:20.210
Uh...how do you feel

10:20.210 --> 10:23.080
about adding an extra wife
to this situation?

10:27.620 --> 10:29.710
I mean, you know,
you always talk about how,

10:29.710 --> 10:31.250
you know, you hate
doing the laundry.

10:31.250 --> 10:33.620
I just feel
we could...you kn--

10:33.620 --> 10:35.210
Okay.
I was just, you know --

10:35.210 --> 10:37.000
Like I said,
I was just, um...

10:37.000 --> 10:38.580
just asking for a friend.

10:38.580 --> 10:42.170
♪♪

10:42.170 --> 10:42.830
Junior:
How's the book, Mom?

10:42.830 --> 10:44.460
Aah! Ah.

10:44.460 --> 10:46.710
Hey. Hey.

10:46.710 --> 10:48.500
Hey, Junior.
It's good.

10:48.500 --> 10:49.620
[ Sighs ]
Yeah.

10:49.620 --> 10:51.120
Yeah, it's really,
really good.

10:51.120 --> 10:53.500
Yeah, it looks like
a real page-turner.
Uh-huh.

10:53.500 --> 10:54.920
It's alright.
Mom, I know
you're a book person,

10:54.920 --> 10:56.710
but you should try this.

10:56.710 --> 10:59.210
VR is an incredible
stress reliever.
Oh, come on.

10:59.210 --> 11:02.000
Okay.

11:02.000 --> 11:03.620
I don't know
if I'm gonna get into this.

11:03.620 --> 11:04.790
Die!

11:04.790 --> 11:06.620
Die, you zombie jerks!

11:06.620 --> 11:07.670
I'll see you in Hell!

11:07.670 --> 11:09.500
[ Grunts ]

11:09.500 --> 11:11.790
This is
all I ever wanted.

11:11.790 --> 11:13.000
[ Imitates explosion ]

11:13.000 --> 11:15.120
It was all happening.

11:15.120 --> 11:18.920
I was on a date with my art mom
and my birth mom.

11:18.920 --> 11:21.380
It was the type of thing
dreams are made of.

11:21.380 --> 11:23.920
♪ My chérie amour ♪

11:23.920 --> 11:25.000
Mmm.
Aww.

11:25.000 --> 11:25.960
♪ Lovely as a summer day ♪

11:25.960 --> 11:27.250
Mmm.
[ Laughs ]

11:27.250 --> 11:29.540
You want some ice cream
with that pie, baby?

11:29.540 --> 11:31.670
Bow says I have to cut back
on the dairy.

11:31.670 --> 11:33.790
[ Laughs ]

11:33.790 --> 11:36.500
You see any Rainbows
around here, Lynette?

11:36.500 --> 11:39.380
Clear skies
from what I can see, Ruby.

11:39.380 --> 11:40.960
Shall we, Dre?
Put it in my mouth.

11:40.960 --> 11:42.830
Ah!

11:42.830 --> 11:44.420
Mmm. Mmm!
[ Laughs ]

11:44.420 --> 11:45.830
Mmm!

11:45.830 --> 11:46.830
Mom mom mom mom.

11:46.830 --> 11:48.750
[ Laughs ]
Yes! Oh!

11:48.750 --> 11:51.880
[ To the tune of "My Chérie
Amour" ] ♪ Mom mom mom mom ♪

11:51.880 --> 11:53.500
♪ Mom mom ♪

11:53.500 --> 11:55.500
Dre. Dre.
Huh? Hmm?

11:55.500 --> 11:57.330
The hell is wrong
with you, boy?

11:57.330 --> 11:59.540
Nothing, Pops.
It's -- It's all good.

11:59.540 --> 12:02.380
It's all very good.

12:02.380 --> 12:03.880
Hey, guys,
where should we start first,

12:03.880 --> 12:05.080
upstairs or downstairs?

12:05.080 --> 12:06.460
Upstairs.
Downstairs.

12:06.460 --> 12:08.210
Okay, you know what?
I'll choose.

12:08.210 --> 12:09.830
Let's go
to the sculpture garden.

12:09.830 --> 12:11.710
Okay.
Okay.

12:13.040 --> 12:14.380
This will be fun.

12:14.380 --> 12:15.580
You just got to get
into the spirit.

12:15.580 --> 12:17.620
[ Sighs ] Why are you so
on board with this?

12:17.620 --> 12:18.880
You think Lynette
is the first woman

12:18.880 --> 12:21.120
to drag me into a museum?

12:21.120 --> 12:22.330
Look, she's not even
the first woman

12:22.330 --> 12:24.080
to drag me
into this museum.

12:24.080 --> 12:26.000
I've learned
as a black man of my age

12:26.000 --> 12:27.250
that there are
certain subjects

12:27.250 --> 12:29.290
that people assume
I know a lot about --

12:29.290 --> 12:31.750
jazz, boxing, ribs,
the war...

12:31.750 --> 12:33.420
Which war?
It doesn't matter.

12:33.420 --> 12:35.380
Once a brother gets a few
gray hairs in his head,

12:35.380 --> 12:37.710
white people just assume
you're wise.

12:37.710 --> 12:40.380
Why do you think Morgan Freeman
has played God so many times?

12:40.380 --> 12:42.210
'Cause he's got
that old Black magic.

12:42.210 --> 12:44.330
So, you could just lie
to people?

12:44.330 --> 12:46.670
No, I don't just lie
to people.

12:46.670 --> 12:48.880
I use their assumptions about me
against them.

12:48.880 --> 12:51.830
Mm, I don't think people
are that gullible, Pops.

12:51.830 --> 12:53.080
Watch and learn, Jack,
my boy.

12:53.080 --> 12:54.500
Watch and learn.

12:54.500 --> 12:59.710
♪♪

12:59.710 --> 13:01.290
This piece leaves me cold.

13:01.290 --> 13:02.710
Well, you have to admit

13:02.710 --> 13:05.460
the artist does have
masterful control of the medium.

13:05.460 --> 13:06.960
You know,
I didn't notice that before.

13:06.960 --> 13:09.380
[ Chuckles ]
Now I feel like an idiot.

13:09.380 --> 13:11.380
Did I see you open
for Herbie Hancock?

13:12.710 --> 13:14.420
I'm just here
with my family today.

13:14.420 --> 13:16.210
So let's just keep it
our secret.

13:16.210 --> 13:18.960
♪♪

13:18.960 --> 13:21.170
The interesting thing
about this piece

13:21.170 --> 13:23.120
is that it's all about
the objectification

13:23.120 --> 13:24.380
of the Black male body.

13:24.380 --> 13:27.920
Mm.
Well, there's not much
to objectify.

13:27.920 --> 13:29.540
Ma-- Mama, come on.

13:29.540 --> 13:33.120
Well, I'm just saying,
there should be a little
more "there" there.

13:33.120 --> 13:34.500
You know what I mean?
[ Laughs ] Amen.

13:34.500 --> 13:36.000
Come on, now.
You know what I'm saying.

13:36.000 --> 13:37.120
"Amen"? Huh?

13:37.120 --> 13:38.540
Like a little,
old penis, okay?

13:40.120 --> 13:42.830
[ Sighs ]
I don't know about you,

13:42.830 --> 13:45.460
but I think this artist shows
amazing control of the medium.

13:45.460 --> 13:47.250
Mm-hmm.
Absolutely.

13:47.250 --> 13:48.920
The medium
is totally controlled.

13:48.920 --> 13:49.880
Amazingly.

13:49.880 --> 13:51.380
[ Chuckles ]
Aww.

13:51.380 --> 13:52.960
That's so adorable.

13:52.960 --> 13:54.670
You kids have no idea
what you're talking about.

13:54.670 --> 13:56.750
Excuse me.

13:56.750 --> 13:58.290
I think what they
meant to say

13:58.290 --> 13:59.580
is that
this particular artist

13:59.580 --> 14:02.500
shows amazing control
of the medium.

14:02.500 --> 14:03.960
Oh.

14:03.960 --> 14:05.670
I see it now.

14:05.670 --> 14:07.080
Hey, I don't know why,

14:07.080 --> 14:10.330
but I feel comfortable
asking you...

14:10.330 --> 14:12.790
I haven't talked to my dad
in 15 years.

14:12.790 --> 14:15.330
Should I call him?

14:15.330 --> 14:17.540
Let's talk about it,
son.

14:17.540 --> 14:20.120
♪♪

14:20.120 --> 14:21.750
And I said, "Well,
in this house,

14:21.750 --> 14:24.040
your name
is O'Shea Jackson,

14:24.040 --> 14:25.960
and no, you cannot have
another soda."

14:25.960 --> 14:26.790
[ Laughter ]

14:26.790 --> 14:28.290
Look at us,

14:28.290 --> 14:30.920
two single mothers
who raised Black sons

14:30.920 --> 14:33.290
in Los Angeles
in the '80s.

14:33.290 --> 14:34.790
Oh, we went through a lot.

14:34.790 --> 14:36.460
Yeah. The riots.

14:36.460 --> 14:37.790
Mm.
O.J.

14:37.790 --> 14:38.920
Ooh.
[ Chuckles ]

14:38.920 --> 14:40.750
The Kobe-Shaq beef.
Mm.

14:40.750 --> 14:43.540
Oh, that one
almost tore my family apart.

14:43.540 --> 14:45.250
But we survived it all.

14:45.250 --> 14:47.830
There should be streets
named after us.

14:47.830 --> 14:49.710
Ruby Boulevard.

14:49.710 --> 14:50.670
Lynette Avenue.

14:50.670 --> 14:52.330
[ Both laugh ]

14:52.330 --> 14:53.960
I know.

14:53.960 --> 14:57.670
Dre, three bread baskets
at The Cheesecake Machine,

14:57.670 --> 15:02.170
and not once did you tell me
all the things we had in common.

15:02.170 --> 15:04.120
Well...
Wait a minute. What was that?

15:04.120 --> 15:06.080
Mama, she's joking,
alright?

15:06.080 --> 15:07.790
We talked about you
the entire time.

15:07.790 --> 15:09.120
No, no, no.
Not that part.

15:09.120 --> 15:11.750
You took her
to The Cheesecake Machine?

15:11.750 --> 15:13.540
Yeah.

15:13.540 --> 15:15.960
The one on Sepulveda?

15:15.960 --> 15:17.830
Yeah. That --
That's the closest one.

15:17.830 --> 15:21.000
You could've taken her to sushi
or some other nonsense,

15:21.000 --> 15:24.960
but instead, you took her
to our place?

15:24.960 --> 15:28.420
If she wants to go, you let
her son Doug take her.

15:28.420 --> 15:30.620
I --
That tacky-ass restaurant

15:30.620 --> 15:33.880
is where you take
your mother!

15:33.880 --> 15:35.040
You betrayed me!

15:38.750 --> 15:41.040
Oh. Oh, oh, oh. Come here.
Oh, I see you, I see you!

15:41.040 --> 15:42.710
[ Grunts ]
Okay, I don't have

15:42.710 --> 15:45.120
the energy
for whatever this is.

15:48.960 --> 15:50.920
So, I had made a mistake

15:50.920 --> 15:53.920
and got too comfortable
with my side mom.

15:53.920 --> 15:55.710
Now there was hell to pay.

15:55.710 --> 15:58.040
Ma?

15:58.040 --> 16:00.120
Brought you some Rolos.

16:00.120 --> 16:02.080
Your favorite.

16:02.080 --> 16:03.960
You can just leave them
on the table.

16:06.750 --> 16:10.500
[ Sighs ]
Look. Hey, Mama.

16:10.500 --> 16:14.460
I'm sorry I took Lynette
to The Cheesecake Machine.

16:14.460 --> 16:15.830
I didn't know.

16:15.830 --> 16:18.540
How could you not know

16:18.540 --> 16:21.460
that The Cheesecake Machine
was our place?

16:21.460 --> 16:24.170
Ma, because
it's everybody's place.

16:24.170 --> 16:26.380
It's the one thing
that everybody agrees on.

16:26.380 --> 16:29.580
If they put one
in the Middle East,

16:29.580 --> 16:32.620
I think everything
would be good.

16:32.620 --> 16:34.620
But still,
it was something special

16:34.620 --> 16:36.540
just between
the two of us.

16:36.540 --> 16:39.000
[ Sighs ]

16:39.000 --> 16:40.250
I don't know
if you've noticed,

16:40.250 --> 16:43.290
but your tastes
have changed.

16:43.290 --> 16:45.420
Ever since you went off
to college

16:45.420 --> 16:51.210
and started experiencing a world
outside of what I know,

16:51.210 --> 16:53.460
I've been losing parts
of you.

16:53.460 --> 16:54.830
Mama, that's not true.

16:54.830 --> 16:56.670
Ah, yes, it is, Dre.

16:56.670 --> 16:59.290
But still...

16:59.290 --> 17:02.710
I guess it's also
just a part of life.

17:02.710 --> 17:06.040
I don't want to be
the reason you don't grow.

17:06.040 --> 17:08.620
I've adjusted to you living
in Sherman Oaks.

17:08.620 --> 17:10.170
Mm.

17:10.170 --> 17:13.460
And I've adjusted to Rainbow
being in the house.

17:13.460 --> 17:15.620
[ Laughs ]

17:15.620 --> 17:17.580
I guess I'm just gonna
have to adjust

17:17.580 --> 17:20.330
to sharing you
with another woman.

17:22.830 --> 17:26.790
I'm glad you've got
an art friend.

17:26.790 --> 17:28.710
You are?
Mm.

17:28.710 --> 17:31.540
I really am.

17:31.540 --> 17:33.000
Come here.

17:33.000 --> 17:37.580
♪♪

17:37.580 --> 17:40.620
These saved your life.

17:40.620 --> 17:42.210
[ Chuckles ]

17:43.500 --> 17:47.420
So, Mom was cool with me
hanging out with Lynette.

17:47.420 --> 17:49.750
But something
still felt off.

17:49.750 --> 17:52.080
♪♪

17:52.080 --> 17:54.380
Alright, Mom,
I have got my headset,

17:54.380 --> 17:56.000
and I'm ready to go.

17:57.580 --> 18:00.920
Uh, Mom, are --
are you dead in the game?

18:00.920 --> 18:03.210
Are you dead in life?

18:03.210 --> 18:04.710
Shh.

18:04.710 --> 18:06.880
Junior,
I beat the game.

18:06.880 --> 18:08.040
I made my way to Catalina

18:08.040 --> 18:10.380
and killed every damn zombie
on this island.

18:10.380 --> 18:12.540
Once I was safe,
I dragged over this couch,

18:12.540 --> 18:15.250
found a copy of my book,
and put my feet up.

18:15.250 --> 18:18.000
Come on.
Join me.

18:18.000 --> 18:19.750
Let's relax together.

18:19.750 --> 18:22.710
Oh, yeah, this is nice!

18:22.710 --> 18:25.580
I bet we could find a golf cart
and go for a joy ride.

18:25.580 --> 18:27.710
I could get
used to it here.

18:27.710 --> 18:30.420
Please, sweetie,
don't make me ice you.

18:30.420 --> 18:32.210
You're right, Mom.
Let's just do it your way.

18:32.210 --> 18:34.580
Let's relax.

18:34.580 --> 18:35.750
Love you.

18:35.750 --> 18:37.580
Love you.

18:37.580 --> 18:40.040
Even though Mama said
she was fine,

18:40.040 --> 18:42.670
I could tell she needed
some more convincing.

18:42.670 --> 18:45.790
Hey, Mama.
Hey.

18:45.790 --> 18:49.170
You remember that poster
I had on my wall as a kid?

18:49.170 --> 18:51.380
You know, the one
from "Good Times"?

18:51.380 --> 18:52.330
Ah, yeah.

18:52.330 --> 18:55.290
The one with
all them Negroes sinning?

18:55.290 --> 18:57.880
[ Chuckles ]
So you do remember it.

18:57.880 --> 19:01.250
Mm-hmm.
You know that was the
first piece of art I owned?

19:01.250 --> 19:03.920
Oh, Dre. You know I only
bought that to cover up

19:03.920 --> 19:05.960
the hole I punched
in your wall

19:05.960 --> 19:07.920
after they canceled
"St. Elsewhere."

19:07.920 --> 19:10.830
[ Chuckles ]
You know,
it doesn't matter why.

19:10.830 --> 19:15.290
What matters is that
no corner of my life

19:15.290 --> 19:17.500
has not been inspired
by you.

19:17.500 --> 19:19.080
Aww.

19:19.080 --> 19:21.500
I mean, Mama, you may not have
taught me about art,

19:21.500 --> 19:25.380
but you showed me how
to be passionate about the arts.

19:25.380 --> 19:29.080
All that time we spent
listening to records,

19:29.080 --> 19:31.210
you don't think
that had an effect on me?

19:31.210 --> 19:32.380
Mm.

19:32.380 --> 19:36.580
Mama, everything I am
is because of you.

19:36.580 --> 19:38.460
Oh, I know.

19:38.460 --> 19:39.380
Mm. Are you sure?

19:39.380 --> 19:40.750
Mm.

19:40.750 --> 19:43.920
Because you will always be
my number-one girl.

19:43.920 --> 19:47.290
Ain't no competition.

19:47.290 --> 19:49.000
So, you don't want
to take Lynette

19:49.000 --> 19:51.960
to the gospel brunch
at the House of Blues?

19:51.960 --> 19:53.620
No, I don't.

19:53.620 --> 19:54.710
Mm.

19:54.710 --> 19:59.750
In fact...
I've cleared my schedule.

19:59.750 --> 20:02.120
So, if you want to go
to the Farmer's Market,

20:02.120 --> 20:04.210
let's go.

20:04.210 --> 20:07.380
If you want to go to church,
let's go.

20:07.380 --> 20:10.000
But it will be just
the two of us.

20:11.960 --> 20:13.120
Alright, then.

20:13.120 --> 20:14.710
I already know.
Hmm?

20:14.710 --> 20:16.830
I want to go
to The Cheesecake Machine.

20:16.830 --> 20:18.750
Done.

20:18.750 --> 20:21.710
In Palm Springs.

20:21.710 --> 20:22.540
Palm Springs?

20:22.540 --> 20:23.750
It's a new one!

20:23.750 --> 20:25.540
They just opened, Dre.

20:25.540 --> 20:29.120
There's not even any graffiti
in the bathroom yet.

20:29.120 --> 20:31.540
Yeah, that's --
that's more of a weekend.

20:31.540 --> 20:34.830
Great! Then we'll make
a whole weekend of it, Dre.

20:34.830 --> 20:36.290
[ Laughs ]

20:36.290 --> 20:37.620
You go tell your wife.

20:37.620 --> 20:39.290
I'll start packing.

20:39.290 --> 20:41.830
Rainbow, we're going away
for the weekend!

20:41.830 --> 20:44.120
You can't come!

20:47.540 --> 20:49.210
And next, we have...

20:49.210 --> 20:53.000
this self portrait
by James Adams.

20:53.000 --> 20:55.120
As with all the other paintings
that we've seen today,

20:55.120 --> 20:57.330
you might notice
that this piece

20:57.330 --> 21:00.210
clearly displays his trademark
control of the medium.

21:00.210 --> 21:01.790
Excuse me.

21:01.790 --> 21:03.750
I don't recognize you.

21:03.750 --> 21:06.040
Are you one
of our docents?

21:06.040 --> 21:08.580
That depends.
What's a docent?

21:08.580 --> 21:10.120
Security?

21:10.120 --> 21:11.960
No need.
I'll let myself out.

21:11.960 --> 21:16.880
Remember, control of the medium
is within all of you.

21:16.880 --> 21:21.380
♪♪

21:21.380 --> 21:23.290
Well, that sucks.
He was our ride.
